tern_Sydney_Wanderers_FC_season"}
{"title_page": "Cavetown (musician)", "text_new": "{{short description|English singer-songwriter (b. 1998)}}\n{{Redirect|Devil Town (song)|the Daniel Johnston song|1990 (Daniel Johnston album)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| background       = solo_singer\n| name             = Cavetown\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1998|12|15|df=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Oxford, England|Oxford]], [[Oxfordshire]], England\n| years_active     = 2012\u2013present\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Indie pop]]<ref name=\"RYM\">{{Cite web|url=https://rateyourmusic.com/artist/cavetown|title=Cavetown discography|website=RateYourMusic|access-date=13 July 2019}}</ref>\n* [[indie folk]]<ref name=\"RYM\" />\n* [[bedroom pop]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thehillnews.org/ae/lexieperlow/cavetown-debuts-with-lemon-boy|title=Cavetown Debuts with 'Lemon Boy'|last=Perlow|first=Lexie|date=19 April 2018|website=The Hill News|url-status=live|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref>\n* [[indie rock]]<ref name=\":13\" />\n}}\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n* Singer-songwriter\n* [[YouTuber]]\n}}\n| instrument       = {{flatlist|\n* Vocals\n* ukulele\n* guitar\n* melodica<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E9ymI-7Rws0|title=Cavetown \u2013 Juliet (Live)|publisher=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=23 January 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Infobox person|child=yes\n| nationality      = British\n| home_town        = [[Cambridge]], [[Cambridgeshire]], England<ref name=\":13\" />\n}}\n| module2          = {{Infobox YouTube personality\n| embed                = yes\n| channel_display_name = cavetown\n| channel_direct_url   = user/fluffybluehat/\n| genre = {{Flatlist|\n* Music\n* [[vlogging]]\n* talk show\n}}\n| subscribers     = 1.2 million\n| subscriber_date = February 2020\n| views           = 140.9 million\n| view_date       = April 2020\n| silver_button   = yes\n| gold_button     = yes\n| child           = yes}}\n| image            = Cavetown Sept 2018.png\n| caption          = Cavetown in a Q&A video in 2018\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Sire Records]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sirerecords.com/artist/cavetown|title=Cavetown|website=[[Sire Records]]|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Triple Crown Records]]<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/release/dear-mr0004952771|title=Dear. \u2013 Cavetown {{!}} Release Credits|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|url-status=live}}</ref>\n}}\n| associated_acts  = {{flatlist|\n* [[mxmtoon]]\n* [[Field Medic]]\n* [[Sidney Gish]]\n* [[Kevin Devine]]\n* [[Chloe Moriondo]]\n* spookyghostboy\n* [[Conan Gray]]\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Robin Daniel Skinner'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ascap.com/repertory#ace/writer/867308113/SKINNER%20ROBIN%20DANIEL|title=ASCAP Ace Search|last=Skinner|first=Robin Daniel|publisher=[[American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers]] (ASCAP)|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref> (born 15 December 1998),<ref name=\":13\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/cavetown-mn0003771881/biography|title=Cavetown {{!}} Biography & History|last=Monger|first=Timothy|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|url-status=live}}</ref> known professionally as '''Cavetown''', is an English singer-songwriter and [[YouTuber]] based in [[Cambridge]]. His style blends elements of [[indie rock]], [[indie pop]] and [[bedroom pop]] with mellow, gentle ukulele ballads.<ref name=\":13\" /> As of February 2020, he has amassed over 3.3&nbsp;million [[List of most-streamed artists on Spotify|monthly streamers]] on [[Spotify]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/artist/2hR4h1Cao2ueuI7Cx9c7V8|title=Cavetown|website=[[Spotify]]|url-status=live}}</ref> His YouTube channel, which he began in November 2012, sits at 1.2 million subscribers and 128.1&nbsp;million video views.<ref name=\":02\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCpLqtJdfhVv58cPFhRzWJlg|title=cavetown|publisher=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=23 January 2020}}</ref> Skinner released his fourth studio album, ''Sleepyhead'', in March 2020.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Cavetown-Releases-Highly-Anticipated-New-Album-SLEEPYHEAD-20200327|title=Cavetown Releases Highly-Anticipated New Album SLEEPYHEAD|last=|first=|date=27 March 2020|website=BroadwayWorld.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nSkinner was born in [[Oxford]] on 15 December 1998 and relocated to [[Cambridge]] at the age of eight.<ref name=\":13\" /> His interest in music was inspired by his father, [[David Skinner (musicologist)|David Skinner]], a professional [[Flute|flautist]] and director of music at [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge University]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theseymourowl.com/4115/features/cavetown-robin-skinner/|title=Cavetown (Robin Skinner)|last=Hughel|first=Phoebe|date=3 April 2019|website=The Owl|url-status=live|access-date=21 July 2019}}</ref> who taught him how to play the acoustic guitar at the age of eight.<ref name=\":22\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cambridgelive.org.uk/tickets/events/cavetown|title=Cavetown|date=22 November 2018|website=Cambridge Live|url-status=live|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> His mother is a professional [[Baroque music|Baroque]] flautist and music teacher. He attended [[Parkside Community College]] and [[Hills Road Sixth Form College]] and received an [[National Citizen Service|NCS]] in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cavetown.co.uk/cv|title=About|website=Cavetown.co.uk|url-status=live|accessdate=23 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n=== 2012\u20132015: YouTube, Bandcamp ===\nSkinner began his YouTube channel in November 2012 and uploaded his first video, an original song named Haunted Lullaby in October 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tmrwmagazine.com/features/legacy/chat-youtuber-artist-cavetown|title=a chat with youtuber and artist, cavetown|last=Ta|first=Kacie|date=26 September 2017|website=Tmrw magazine|url-status=live|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=- Haunted Lullaby -|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YH5gw0G7Ebw|language=en|access-date=2019-12-13}}</ref> Skinner began recording, producing and releasing music to [[Bandcamp]] in 2013, and had released his first album, ''Everything Is Made of Clouds'', to the platform at the age of 14.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://reviewsmagazine.net/the-music-of-cavetown-a-helping-hand-for-mental-health-issues/|title=The Music of Cavetown: A Helping Hand for Mental Health Issues {{!}} Re:Views Magazine|last=Minaeva|first=Mariia|date=12 December 2018|website=Reviews Magazine|url-status=live|access-date=13 July 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":32\">{{Cite web|url=https://cavetown.bandcamp.com/album/everything-is-made-of-clouds|title=Everything is Made of Clouds \u2013 cavetown|website=[[BandCamp]]|url-status=live}}</ref> Skinner released ''Gd Vibes'', ''Nervous Friends // Pt. 1'', ''Balance'' (as ''brother'') and ''Everything is Made of Stars'' on Bandcamp over the following two years.<ref name=\":42\">{{Cite web|url=https://cavetown.bandcamp.com/album/gd-vibes|title=Gd vibes \u2013 cavetown|website=[[Bandcamp]]|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":52\">{{Cite web|url=https://cavetown.bandcamp.com/album/nervous-friends-pt-1|title=Nervous Friends // Pt. 1 \u2013 cavetown|website=[[Bandcamp]]|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/cavetown/wiki/albums|title=Album Information|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2 January 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":62\">{{Cite web|url=https://cavetown.bandcamp.com/album/everything-is-made-of-stars|title=Everything is Made of Stars \u2013 cavetown|website=[[Bandcamp]]|url-status=live}}</ref> Critics expressed that they felt \"the acceptance of ignorance\" on ''Gd Vibes''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.divideandconquermusic.com/1/post/2015/01/cavetown-gd-vibes.html|title=cavetown \u2013 Gd vibes|last=Rogen|first=Ted|date=15 January 2015|website=Insight & Critique|url-status=live|access-date=15 September 2019}}</ref> Skinner released his debut single \"This Is Home\" in August 2015, which has reached over 43 million streams on Spotify,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/this-is-home-single/1343956529|title=This Is Home \u2013 Single by Cavetown|website=[[Apple Music]]|url-status=live}}</ref> before releasing his debut self-titled album in November 2015.<ref name=\":72\">{{Cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/cavetown/1344004465|title=Cavetown \u2013 Cavetown|website=[[Apple Music]]|url-status=live}}</ref> Critics described the album ''cavetown'' as \"an eclectic mix of acoustic and electronic\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.badluck.co/blog/newmusic/listen-to-cavetowns-latest-ep|title=Listen to Cavetown's latest EP|date=9 November 2015|website=Bad Luck|url-status=live|access-date=15 September 2019}}</ref> Skinner continued to publish covers of songs onto his YouTube channel from artists such as [[Pinegrove (band)|Pinegrove]], [[Twenty One Pilots]] and [[Joji (musician)|Joji]].<ref name=\":22\" />\n\n=== 2016\u20132018: ''Lemon Boy''===\nIn 2016, Skinner released his second studio album, ''16/04/16.''<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/16-04-16/1348540876|title=16/04/06 \u2013 Cavetown|website=[[Apple Music]]|url-status=live}}</ref> The album includes a mix of \"warm, melodic [[bedroom pop]]\" and \"lo-fi [[indie rock]]\".<ref name=\":13\" /> In April 2017, whilst still at Sixth Form College, Skinner made it through to the final of the Cambridge Band Competition winning both Best Acoustic Act and the [[Kimberley Rew]] Award for Songwriting and going on to play at [[Strawberry Fair]] in June 2017. In 2018, he released his third album, ''Lemon Boy''. The album's title track has amassed 24 million streams on Spotify and nearly 10&nbsp;million views on YouTube as of September 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://musicexistence.com/blog/2019/09/13/cavetown-shares-new-single-telescope/|title=Cavetown shares new single \"Telescope\"|last=Hutchings|first=John|date=13 September 2019|website=Music Existence|url-status=live|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== 2019\u2013present: ''Animal Kingdom'' and ''Sleepyhead''===\n[[File:Cavetown in Vienna August 2019.jpg|left|thumb|239x239px|Cavetown in [[Vienna]] in August 2019]]\nIn 2019, Skinner released five split singles which were later compiled into ''Animal Kingdom'', a mixtape of ten tracks including covers and original singles with guest appearances from [[Sidney Gish]], Simi, [[Chloe Moriondo]] and Spookyghostboy.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stereogum.com/2037584/sidney-gish-somebodys-baby-jackson-browne-cover/music/|title=Sidney Gish Covers Jackson Browne's \"Somebody's (Jackson Baby Browne Cover)|last=Rettig|first=James|date=28 March 2018|website=[[Stereogum]]|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://closedcap.com/2019/01/09/cavetown-impresses-on-latest-drop/|title=Cavetown Can't Stop|date=9 January 2019|website=Closed Captioned|url-status=live|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> He produced the single \"[[The Masquerade (mxmtoon album)#Track listing|prom dress]]\" by [[mxmtoon]], which has gained over 8 million streams on Spotify and has been used in over 100,000 videos on the video-sharing platform, [[TikTok]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/mxmtoon-breaks-down-the-meaning-of-prom-dress|title=Mxmtoon Breaks Down The Meaning of 'Prom Dress'|last=Thioubou|first=Ndeye|date=25 June 2019|website=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|url-status=live|access-date=15 September 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"BW\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/mxmtoon-Gives-Personal-Insight-in-New-Single-seasonal-depression-20190719|title=mxmtoon Gives Personal Insight in New Single 'seasonal depression'|website=[[BroadwayWorld]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190721102337/https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/mxmtoon-Gives-Personal-Insight-in-New-Single-seasonal-depression-20190719|archive-date=21 July 2019|access-date=21 July 2019|quote=mxmtoon is a 19-year-old bourgeoning artist|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Wells\">{{Cite news|url=https://thebolditalic.com/meet-mxmtoon-the-oakland-teen-who-launched-her-music-career-on-tiktok-749613d28947|title=Meet mxmtoon, the Oakland Teen Who Launched Her Music Career on TikTok|last=Wells|first=Madeline|date=4 August 2019|work=[[The Bold Italic]]|access-date=4 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190904163451/https://thebolditalic.com/meet-mxmtoon-the-oakland-teen-who-launched-her-music-career-on-tiktok-749613d28947?gi=ddaa61d9ba06|archive-date=4 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The single featured on mxmtoon's debut album ''[[The Masquerade (mxmtoon album)|the masquerade]]'' which was also fully produced by Skinner.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/112082837|title=the masquerade / mxmtoon|publisher=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|accessdate=November 1, 2019}}</ref> Skinner performed on the Acoustic Stage at [[Victorious Festival]] in August 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiox.co.uk/festivals/victorious-festival/victorious-festival-stage-times-line-up-more/|title=Victorious Festival: Stage Times, Line-Up & More|date=25 August 2019|website=[[Radio X (United Kingdom)|Radio X]]|url-status=live}}</ref> He signed under [[Sire Records]] in 2019 where he released the single \"Telescope\" ahead of his upcoming album, later announced as ''Sleepyhead''.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Cavetown-Releases-New-Song-via-Sire-Records-20190913|title=Cavetown Releases New Song via Sire Records|date=13 September 2019|website=[[BroadwayWorld]]|url-status=live|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> Skinner embarked on a series of sold-out worldwide headlining tours in October 2019. He played on tour at 31 venues in the US and 15 venues in the UK over the space of four months.<ref name=\":0\" /> He was joined by [[Hunny (band)|Hunny]] and mxmtoon for a few shows in the UK tour,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upsetmagazine.com/news/hunny-and-cavetown-are-teaming-up-for-a-uk-tour-early-next-year|title=Hunny and Cavetown are teaming up for a UK tour early next year|date=September 25, 2019|website=Upset Magazine|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=October 7, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/live/mxmtoon-confirms-first-uk-appearances|title=mxmtoon Confirms First UK Appearances|last=Murray|first=Robin|date=June 4, 2019|website=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=2019-10-07}}</ref> as well as [[Field Medic]] and [[Chloe Moriondo]] for a few shows in the US tour.<ref name=\":0\" /> In October 2019, Skinner announced his headlining tour along [[Australia]]'s east coast which took place in January 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.warnermusic.com.au/news/cavetown-announces-2020-australia-tour|title=CAVETOWN ANNOUNCES 2020 AUSTRALIA TOUR|website=[[Warner Music Australasia]]|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=2019-10-07}}</ref>\n\nIn 2020, Skinner released his major label debut album ''Sleepyhead''.<ref name=\":5\" />\n\n== Artistry ==\n=== Musical style and songwriting ===\nSkinner is known for his \"gentle ukulele ballads\" and \"melodic bedroom pop\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.onestowatch.com/artist/cavetown|title=Cavetown \u2013 Singer-Songwriter|website=Ones To Watch|access-date=13 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nAs of November 2018, Skinner lives in [[Cambridge]], England.<ref name=\":22\"/> He has identified himself as \"somewhere on the [[Asexuality|Ace]] and [[Aromantic|Aro]] spectrums\" in an autobiographical [[Tumblr]] post.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://nice-worm.tumblr.com/faq|title=frequently asked questions|last=cavetown|website=[[Tumblr]]|url-status=live|access-date=November 1, 2019}}</ref> Skinner publicly dated Avery Vernon from September 2019 to March 2020.<ref>{{Cite tweet|number=1173762105893433344|user=CAVETOWN|title=Yeah him my Boyfriend now but my point still stands that boys can be affectionate without being in a relationship :)|author=cavetown|date=September 17, 2019}}</ref> In an interview with [[Urban Outfitters]], he stated, \"I got a boyfriend recently, I'm very excited about it and I like him and I'm going to write a song about him sometime\".<ref>{{Citation|title=Cavetown Talks About His Cursed Furby \u2014 Open Up|date=October 25, 2019|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8OPXSWTmmjw|work=[[Urban Outfitters|Urban Outfitters Television]]|language=en|access-date=November 1, 2019}}</ref> In early March, Vernon confirmed that he and Skinner were no longer in a relationship on [[Twitter]], stating, \"robin and i are no longer dating and i'm only announcing this because it's been exhausting seeing us both tagged in things. we are still very close and always will be, we both just need time to heal :) thank u for understanding\".<ref>{{Cite tweet|number=1236625986407579650|user=lil__benadryl|title=robin and i are no longer dating and i'm only announcing this because it's been exhausting seeing us both tagged in things. we are still very close and always will be, we both just need time to heal :) thank u for understanding|last=Vernon|first=Avery|date=March 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n=== Studio albums ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:23em;\"| Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[UK Albums Chart|UK]]<br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/56842/cavetown/|title=Cavetown {{!}} full Official Chart History|publisher=Official Charts Company|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Cavetown''\n|\n